  "lemmas": {
    "OPEN": {
      "name": "OPEN_cross_high_residual_and_Mpad",
      "statement": "(1) Separate residual free-1 highs without blowing the e\u00b7p budget (or prove residual top-seam pairs use one high / O(1) highs).\n(2) M_pad\u22641 at free_core=846161.\nTogether with within-family (\u03b9,\u03b4) this closes |A_SP|\u2264t\u00b7p.",
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    "disjoint": {
      "name": "free1_high_families_pairwise_disjoint",
      "proof": [
        "Write \u039b_U(X) = X^e + H_1 X^{e\u22121} + \u22ef + H_{e\u22121} X + c0(U) (high H fixed across F_H).",
        "If r \u2208 U then \u039b_U(r) = 0 \u21d2 H(r) + c0(U) = 0 \u21d2 c0(U) = \u2212H(r), where H(r) means the evaluation of the high part at r.",
        "Thus any root r determines c0 uniquely for that high, hence determines \u039b_U uniquely, hence determines U uniquely among F_H.",
        "Therefore no r can lie in two distinct members of F_H."
      ],
      "statement": "Fix a free-1 high H (the e\u22121 middle coefficients of a monic degree-e locator). Let F_H be the set of e-subsets U \u2282 D whose monic locator has free-1 high H and is fully split on D. Then the members of F_H are pairwise disjoint: U \u2260 U' in F_H \u21d2 U \u2229 U' = \u2205.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "payment": {
      "deployed_e_p": 143763024447376,
      "deployed_floor_n_e": 31,
      "name": "payment_reduction_cross_high_gap",
      "proof": [
        "v24: (U,\u03b4) injects pairs into FS_1(e)\u00d7F_p^\u00d7.",
        "Within F_H: (\u03b9,\u03b4) injects into [e]\u00d7F_p when |F_H|\u2264e.",
        "Single residual high \u21d2 global (\u03b9,\u03b4) works.",
        "Multiple highs: (\u03b9,\u03b4) may collide across highs (toy bank)."
      ],
      "statement": "If M_pad\u22641 and residual free-1 CS ordered pairs all lie in a single free-1 high family F_H, then (U,V) \u21a6 (\u03b9(U), \u03b4) injects them into [e]\u00d7F_p (size e\u00b7p=t\u00b7p deployed), hence |A_SP| \u2264 t\u00b7p.\nMore generally, if residual highs can be injectively tagged by a label in a set of size 1 (one residual high), same conclusion.\nOPEN gap: cross-high collisions of (\u03b9,\u03b4) when many residual highs.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "size": {
      "deployed_e": 67472,
      "deployed_floor_le_e": true,
      "deployed_floor_n_over_e": 31,
      "name": "free1_high_family_size_le_n_over_e",
      "proof": [
        "Pairwise disjoint e-sets in a domain of size n \u21d2 at most \u230an/e\u230b of them.",
        "Previous lemma."
      ],
      "statement": "For every free-1 high H: |F_H| \u2264 \u230an/e\u230b. Deployed: \u230an/e\u230b = \u230a2097152/67472\u230b = 31 \u2264 e = 67472.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "within_marks": {
      "name": "within_high_family_pair_marks",
      "proof": [
        "Free-1 CS \u21d4 same free-1 high and distinct constants.",
        "c0 injective: monic (H,c0) determines U among fully split.",
        "Given (c0U,\u03b4): c0V=c0U\u2212\u03b4; \u039b_U, \u039b_V determined by (H,c0); recover U,V. So (c0U,\u03b4) injective within F_H.",
        "\u03b9 injective \u21d2 (\u03b9(U),\u03b4) injective within F_H.",
        "Size: |F_H| \u2264 \u230an/e\u230b \u2264 e deployed \u21d2 \u03b9(U) \u2208 [e]."
      ],
      "statement": "Free-1 CS ordered pairs (U,V) always share a high H. Inside F_H:\n  \u2022 c0: F_H \u2192 F_p is injective (monic recovery);\n  \u2022 (c0U, \u03b4) with \u03b4=c0U\u2212c0V injects ordered pairs in F_H \u00d7 F_H;\n  \u2022 any bijection \u03b9: F_H \u2192 {0,...,|F_H|\u22121} (e.g. sort by c0) gives (\u03b9(U), \u03b4) injective on ordered pairs inside F_H.\nDeployed |F_H| \u2264 31 \u2264 e \u21d2 \u03b9 lands in [e].",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
